; The term 'project metrics' refers to the quantitative measurements used to evaluate project performance, which may include version count, code complexity, and test coverage.; 
; 'Defects' in this context refer to bugs or issues found in the project code, and 'user interactions' refer to the access events recorded in the access logs.; 
; A 'top-level project' is a project that does not have a client_id, indicating it is not a sub-project of another project.

